summary.p:
Creates a mailbox in Exchange Server 2000 or Exchange Server 2003.
The Alias and HomeMDB parameters must be provided.
The follwing three store parameters are optional and specified in KiloByte (KB).
The StoreQuota defines the limit when Exchange Server issues a warning regards the mailbox size.
The OverQuotaLimit defines the limit when Exchange Server prohibts sending email from this mailbox.
The HardLimit defines the limit to prohibit sending and receiving email.

This method requires that following attributes are selected in the attribute inclusion list:
1. For Alias: mailNickname
2. For HomeMDB: homeMDB
3. If mailbox limits are used: mDBStorageQuota, mDBOverQuotaLimit, mDBOverHardQuotaLimit and mDBUseDefaults
4. msExchMailboxSecurityDescriptor
